# Editing rules: code, config, workflow

## Code and config

- **Macros**: No custom event loop in macros. Build StChain, Init(), loop over Make(i), Finish(). The macro that uses the Maker must be compiled (`.L anaXxx.C+`) and linked to the Maker lib via `AddLinkedLibs` in the runner. See [PHILOSOPHY.md](PHILOSOPHY.md) (two macros section).
- **Makers**: Implement Init(), Make(), Clear(), Finish(). Use ConfigManager for cuts and GetHistConfigPath() for hist YAML. Create histograms in DeclareHistograms(), write in WriteHistograms()/Finish().
- **Config**: Prefer YAML and existing keys; avoid recompiling Makers when only cut/hist values change. New analysis: copy mainconf + maker/hist/cuts YAMLs and point mainconf's `analysis:` to the right analysis_info file.
- **analysis_info**: Used by setup.sh and joblist generator. Keep anaName, workDir, baseRunMacro, baseAnaMacro, mainConf, jobName, scratchSubdir, outputFileStem, nFiles, and starTag in sync (YAML alias recommended). See [docs/REFERENCE.md](docs/REFERENCE.md) (Analysis info).

## Adding content

- **New analysis**: Add StMaker, Makefile target for lib, run_anaXxx.C + anaXxx.C, run_anaXxx.sh, mainconf + analysis_info (and referenced YAMLs). Then generate joblist and update docs per **update-readme-scripts**.
- **New script in script/ or job/run/**: Document in [docs/REFERENCE.md](docs/REFERENCE.md) (directory layout, how to run). Update [README.md](README.md) index if needed. When adding or changing scripts, follow the **update-readme-scripts** skill so the clone-to-run flow stays clear.
- **lib/**: Generated by make; do not commit. Build after `source script/setup.sh <mainconf>`.

## README updates

When adding or changing scripts or the submit/run/QA workflow, update [docs/REFERENCE.md](docs/REFERENCE.md), [INSTALL.md](INSTALL.md) if onboarding steps change, [README.md](README.md) if the doc index changes, and [job/run/README.md](job/run/README.md). Use the **update-readme-scripts** skill for the checklist and structure.
